---
// /promise/ — the Orionfold gating philosophy (Relay D5 ask, 2026-07-01). A
// product-neutral, top-level page that publishes the standing promise the whole
// catalog is held to: buyer-based gating + never-regress. Core/direct use stays
// free; paid Packs sell maintained content; paid Host covers managed customer
// operations; nothing that ever shipped free regresses to paid.
//
// Content source: strategy relay `strategy/relay/_RELAY.md` entry
// "2026-07-01 (later-2) — Relay→Website" ask D5. The promise text is owned by
// the site (we own the promise, Relay owns the CLI behavior it describes). The
// concrete proof point (two engine gaps found while building Agency Pro shipped
// free in the same release that sells the pack) and the four anti-patterns are
// verbatim-safe-to-state facts from that entry. Voice: grade 3-5, jargon
// explained, no em-dashes (website-copy-style).
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import SectionLabel from '../components/ui/SectionLabel.astro';
import { SITE, PUBLISHER } from '../data/seo';
import { ogMeta } from '../data/og';

const og = ogMeta('/promise/');

// The three ideas that make up the promise, stated plainly up top.
const summaryCards = [
  {
    title: 'Core and direct use are free',
    body: 'The engine, direct Cells, installers, schedulers, and public Cell image ship free for everyone. A managed Host right is separate and never makes the free path a trial.',
  },
  {
    title: 'You pay for content',
    body: 'A paid pack is maintained content that uses those free capabilities: ready-made agents, blueprints, and setups we keep current for you. You are buying the upkeep, not the ability to run it.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Nothing regresses',
    body: 'Anything that ever shipped free stays free. We do not move a working, free capability behind a paywall later. What you can do today, you can always do.',
  },
];

// The standing test, expanded. Each section is one plain claim + the reasoning.
const sections = [
  {
    title: 'Buyer-based gating, not feature-based',
    paragraphs: [
      'Most software decides what you can do by which plan you are on. We decide it by whether you bought a specific pack. That is the whole gate: one thing you own, checked once, and then the pack is yours.',
      'There is no tier that turns the free engine into a working product. Direct use is complete and free. A Pack license adds maintained content. A Relay Host license separately covers managed customer Cells. Neither takes the free path away.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Never-regress: free stays free',
    paragraphs: [
      'This is the promise we hold ourselves to the hardest. If a capability ever shipped to everyone for free, it does not later become paid. We will not take something you rely on and put a price on it.',
      'Here is a real example. While building the first paid pack, the Agency pack, we found the engine was missing two things: packs could not add their own triggers, and blueprints could not be scheduled. We shipped both of those free, for every user, in the very same release that put the paid pack on sale. The capability went to everyone. The pack is what you buy.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'What a license actually gates',
    paragraphs: [
      'A Pack license unlocks the premium packs you own and keeps them current. A Relay Host license proves the separate right to run managed customer Cells within its signed capacity. Neither switches on Relay Core or direct Cells, and the public Cell image needs no license token.',
      'Your packs are yours forever. If a license lapses, everything you installed keeps working exactly as it did. Renewal is only about getting the year’s new and updated packs and priority support, never about keeping what you already own.',
      'If a Host term ends, Cells already running keep running and export and recovery remain available. New managed capacity, forward paid updates and re-download stop. Compatible critical-security fixes remain included.',
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'What we will never do',
    paragraphs: [
      'So the promise is concrete, here are the things we have decided against, on purpose:',
    ],
    bullets: [
      'No database licensing. Your right to use what you own is not a row we can flip off.',
      'No upsell banners in the command-line tool. The software you run does not nag you to buy.',
      'No online re-validation. The license is checked offline; your software never sends your data to Orionfold, and it never has to check in with us to keep working.',
      'No expiry that disables installed packs. When a term ends, your installed packs keep running.',
    ],
  },
];
---
<Layout
  title="Our promise: what you pay for, and what you never lose · Orionfold"
  description="The Orionfold promise: Relay Core and direct use stay free, premium Packs and managed Host rights stay distinct, and nothing that shipped free regresses to paid."
  ogImage={og.image}
  ogImageAlt={og.alt}
  jsonLd={[
    {
      '@context': 'https://schema.org',
      '@type': 'WebPage',
      name: 'Our promise · Orionfold',
      url: `${SITE.url}/promise/`,
      inLanguage: 'en',
      publisher: PUBLISHER,
      description:
        'The Orionfold promise: Relay Core and direct use stay free, premium Packs and managed Host rights stay distinct, and nothing that shipped free regresses to paid.',
    },
    {
      '@context': 'https://schema.org',
      '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
      itemListElement: [
        { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: SITE.url },
        { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Promise', item: `${SITE.url}/promise/` },
      ],
    },
  ]}
>
  <Nav />
  <main>
    <section class="relative overflow-hidden px-6 pt-32 pb-18">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none">
        <div class="absolute left-1/2 top-14 h-[26rem] w-[26rem] -translate-x-1/2 rounded-full bg-primary/[0.10] blur-[150px]"></div>
        <div class="absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 h-40" style="background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent, var(--color-surface-raised));"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-5xl">
        <div data-animate>
          <SectionLabel text="Our promise" />
        </div>
        <div class="mt-5 grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.2fr)_18rem] lg:items-end">
          <div>
            <h1 data-animate class="font-display text-[clamp(2.2rem,6vw,4.5rem)] leading-[1.02]" style="transition-delay: 80ms">
              What you pay for, and what you never lose.
            </h1>
            <p data-animate class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-text-muted" style="transition-delay: 160ms">
              Relay Core and direct use are free for everyone. Premium Packs sell maintained content. Relay Host covers managed customer operations. Anything that ships free stays free. This page is the standing promise we hold every product to.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div data-animate class="rounded-2xl border border-primary/30 bg-primary/[0.06] p-5 shadow-[0_20px_80px_-40px_rgba(0,0,0,0.75)]" style="transition-delay: 220ms">
            <p class="font-mono text-[0.62rem] uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary/70">The short version</p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-text">
              Core and direct use stay free. Packs and managed Host rights are separate. Nothing free becomes paid.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-y border-border bg-surface-raised px-6 py-10">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-4 md:grid-cols-3" data-animate-stagger>
        {summaryCards.map((card) => (
          <article data-animate class="rounded-2xl border border-border/70 bg-surface/80 p-5">
            <p class="font-mono text-[0.6rem] uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-primary">{card.title}</p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">{card.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="px-6 py-18">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[15rem_minmax(0,1fr)]">
        <aside data-animate class="lg:sticky lg:top-28 h-fit rounded-2xl border border-border bg-surface-raised/70 p-5">
          <p class="font-mono text-[0.62rem] uppercase tracking-[0.24em] text-text-dim">Why this is written down</p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
            A promise you cannot point to is not a promise. So we put ours on a page, in plain words, and hold every product to it. If we ever break it, you have this to hold us to.
          </p>
        </aside>

        <div class="space-y-5" data-animate-stagger>
          {sections.map((section) => (
            <section data-animate class="rounded-2xl border border-border bg-surface-raised/70 p-6 sm:p-8">
              <h2 class="text-2xl">{section.title}</h2>
              <div class="mt-4 space-y-4">
                {section.paragraphs.map((paragraph) => (
                  <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-text-muted">{paragraph}</p>
                ))}
                {section.bullets && (
                  <ul class="space-y-3 pt-2">
                    {section.bullets.map((bullet) => (
                      <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-text-muted">
                        <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 rounded-full bg-primary"></span>
                        <span>{bullet}</span>
                      </li>
                    ))}
                  </ul>
                )}
              </div>
            </section>
          ))}

          <div data-animate class="rounded-2xl border border-primary/30 bg-primary/[0.06] p-6 sm:p-8">
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-text">
              This promise runs across the whole line. See it in practice on
              <a href="/relay/" class="text-primary hover:text-primary/80 transition-colors">Relay</a>,
              where the engine is free and open and a license only adds the premium packs you own.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
